# Dark Mode Text Contrast

When styling in dark mode, never use black (or near-black) text on black (or near-black) backgrounds.

- Avoid `text-black`, `#000`, `rgb(0,0,0)`, or similar on dark backgrounds.
- Ensure text colors maintain clear contrast against dark surfaces.

```css
/* ❌ BAD */
.title {
  color: #000;
  background: #000;
}

/* ✅ GOOD */
.title {
  color: #e6e6e6;
  background: #0a0a0a;
}
```
